# {{OP_NAME}} SPEC

## 1. Overview / 概述
State the operator purpose, externally observable behavior, and relationship to the source PRD.

{{OVERVIEW}}

## 2. Scope / 范围
Define the functional scope, supported use cases, and explicitly excluded behavior.

{{SCOPE}}

## 3. Supported Platforms / 支持的NPU平台
Specify the target NPU platform scope and any platform-level compatibility constraints.

{{SUPPORTED_PLATFORMS}}

## 4. Operator Interface / 算子接口
Define the operator interface using three canonical forms: the PyTorch ATen IR schema, a pure Python API signature, and a framework-independent pure C++ function signature. Each parameter must be accompanied by a precise semantic specification, including its functional role, tensor semantics, shape and dtype constraints, layout requirements, aliasing/mutability behavior, default values, and optionality semantics where relevant.

{{OPERATOR_INTERFACE}}

## 5. Input Specification / 输入规格
Define each input operand, including rank, shape, dtype, layout, value domain, optionality, and aliasing requirements when applicable.

{{INPUT_SPECIFICATION}}

## 6. Output Specification / 输出规格
Define each output value, including shape, dtype, layout, value domain, aliasing behavior, and determinism guarantees when applicable.

{{OUTPUT_SPECIFICATION}}

## 7. Attribute Specification / 属性规格
Define each operator attribute, including type, default value, valid range, interpretation, and interaction with inputs.

{{ATTRIBUTE_SPECIFICATION}}

## 8. Mathematical Semantics / 数学语义
Define the operator as a pure mathematical mapping over its input domains using rigorous notation and LaTeX formulas.

{{MATHEMATICAL_SEMANTICS}}

## 9. Functional Semantics / 功能语义
Specify the observable functional behavior, execution-independent rules, and equivalence to reference semantics.

{{FUNCTIONAL_SEMANTICS}}

## 10. Numeric Semantics / 数值语义
Specify precision, rounding, overflow, underflow, NaN, Inf, signed zero, and tolerance behavior when applicable.

{{NUMERIC_SEMANTICS}}

## 11. Shape Semantics / Shape 语义
Specify output shape derivation, broadcasting, reduction, reshape, rank, and symbolic dimension rules.

{{SHAPE_SEMANTICS}}

## 12. Data Type Support / 数据类型支持
Specify supported, unsupported, and promotion-related dtype behavior for inputs, attributes, and outputs.

{{DATA_TYPE_SUPPORT}}

## 13. Layout and Format Constraints / Layout 与 Format 约束
Specify accepted memory layouts, tensor formats, contiguity requirements, and layout preservation or conversion behavior.

{{LAYOUT_FORMAT_CONSTRAINTS}}

## 14. Boundary Cases / 边界场景
Specify behavior for boundary inputs such as empty tensors, zero-sized dimensions, scalar tensors, extreme values, and degenerate shapes.

{{BOUNDARY_CASES}}

## 15. Error Handling / 错误处理
Specify validation failures, unsupported cases, diagnostic requirements, and error behavior exposed to callers.

{{ERROR_HANDLING}}

## 16. Compatibility / 兼容性说明
Specify compatibility requirements with reference frameworks, prior versions, aliases, overloads, and documented deviations.

{{COMPATIBILITY}}

## 17. Performance Requirements / 性能要求
Specify measurable performance requirements or state that no additional performance requirement is established by the PRD.

{{PERFORMANCE_REQUIREMENTS}}

## 18. Acceptance Criteria / 验收标准
Specify verifiable criteria for functional correctness, numeric conformance, shape inference, dtype coverage, error handling, and documentation completeness.

{{ACCEPTANCE_CRITERIA}}

## 19. Open Issues / 待确认问题
List unresolved specification issues, or explicitly state that there are no open issues.

{{OPEN_ISSUES}}
